Imagine you are building a game and want to spawn 5 enemies. You could write:

```java
System.out.println("Spawn Enemy");
System.out.println("Spawn Enemy");
System.out.println("Spawn Enemy");
System.out.println("Spawn Enemy");
System.out.println("Spawn Enemy");
```
It works for 5. But what if you need 10,000 enemies? You can't write 10,000 lines of code!
